Fernando is in Istanbul
Fernando Francisco Reges, the Brazilian football player with whom Galatasaray has begun negotiating for a transfer, arrived in Istanbul.
Landing at Atatürk Airport, fans joyfully welcomed the Brazilian football player.
Cheering and chanting in a display of fan support, Fernando left the airport in a private car under security measures.
Starting his career in Brazil’s Vila Nova team and going on to wear the uniforms of Estrela Amadora, Porto and Manchester City, the thirty year old Fernando plays in the midfield.
After going through the medical check, the Brazilian football player is expected to sign a contract with Galatasaray.
